This solution uses the mathematical property of logarithms: if n is a power of 3, then log3(n) must be an integer. We use the Math.log() function to compute the base-3 logarithm of n. If the absolute difference between this value and its rounded value is less than a small constant (1e-10), we consider them as equal, and n is a power of three.

